    "notes":  [
                  "The staged dynamic-universe baseline is retained, and the new r8 system keeps the r4 reentry permissioning, the r5 fragile-cluster guard, the r6 weak-technology weight cap and the r7 MIE removal, then adds a narrow uranium EXIT_NOT_TARGET guard: underwater uranium names can defer a non-PP full exit when they are already in a deep drawdown pocket, which avoids some historically harmful forced sells into later rebounds.",
                  "This system baseline is measured with the same conservative no-lookahead proxy replay, now made reproducible from a machine-readable staged activation map: AXTI activates on 2016-10-04, 006800.KS on 2017-07-03, and 0568.HK on its first real discovery snapshot on 2026-03-27.",
                  "UEC remains selected for removal in the live overlay, but historical swap-removal timing is not replayed because old selector outputs are not stored; this keeps the baseline conservative rather than inflated.",
                  "The retained r8 configuration keeps the successful r2 anti-churn / held-release logic, the r4 permission layer on pullback reentry, the r5 dynamic crypto-beta cluster guard, the r6 weak-technology weight cap and the r7 MIE removal. The promoted change is a very narrow uranium non-PP exit deferral, because the latest decline-phase study showed that some uranium EXIT_NOT_TARGET sells were still happening too deep into local damage and were costing later rebounds.",
                  "Versus the fixed 183-ticker active universe measured with the same engine logic, the r7 staged system improves the full-period replay by +518486.80 ROI points, +18.74 CAGR points, and +0.1653 Sharpe, while also slightly improving full-period drawdown and still improving OOS strongly.",
                  "The key structural gain now comes from not force-selling a few convex uranium names too cheaply during deep drawdown pockets: the r8 guard improves the staged replay full-period CAGR and Sharpe, improves OOS and recent ROI/Sharpe, and does so with only a very small giveback in OOS drawdown."
              ],
